.FILL.JUST
.INDEX <TITO <DEVICE <COMMAND
^^
.INDEX <TITO <DEVICE <COMMAND
.CENTER
THE DEVICE COMMAND
.CENTER
------------------
\\
.PARA
^THE <DEVICE COMMAND CAN BE USED TO CHANGE THE TAPE DRIVES OR DRIVE
DENSITY SETTING WITHOUT QUITING FROM <TITO. ^IT HAS THE FORM
.NOFILL.NOJUST
^^
.SKIP 1
          DEVICE DEVNAME DENSITY(CR)
.FILL.JUST
\\
.SKIP 1
WHERE <DEVNAME AND <DENSITY ARE OPTIONAL. ^IF  <DEVNAME  IS
MISSING,  THE  CURRENT  DEVICE  IS  IMPLIED;  IF <DEVNAME IS
PRESENT, <TITO ATTEMPTS TO USE THIS DEVICE. ^IF <DENSITY  IS
MISSING, THE COMMAND MERELY PRINTS ALL KNOWN CHARACTERISTICS
OF THE DEVICE (OR INTERROGATES THE OPERATOR FOR THEM IF  THE
DEVICE  IS  A  NEW  ONE  UNKNOWN  TO <TITO). ^IF <DENSITY IS
PRESENT, THEN <TITO WILL ATTEMPT TO SET THAT DENSITY AND  ASK
FOR  IT  TO  BE REENTERED IF THE DEVICE IS INCAPABLE OF THIS
DENSITY SETTING.
.INDEX <TITO <MISCELLANEOUS <COMMANDS
.SKIP 1
^^
.CENTER
MISCELLANEOUS COMMANDS
.CENTER
----------------------
\\
.PARA
^THE <WHERE COMMAND PRINTS THE LAST TAPE POSITION NUMBER READ.
^THE TAPE WILL PROBABLY BE POSITIONED A FEW RECORDS PAST THIS
POSITION NUMBER. <TITO PRINTS "POSITION UNKNOWN" IF THE  CURRENT
POSITION NUMBER  IS MEANINGLESS. ^ANOTHER WAY TO GET YOUR
CURRENT POSITION NUMBER IS TO TYPE '^W(CR)' WHEN PROMPTED FOR TAPE
POSITION RANGE DURING THE <RESTORE OR <GET COMMANDS.
^BE ADVISED THIS COMMAND IS SOMEWHAT UNTRUSTWORTHY AND SHOULD NOT
BE USED FOR DETERMINING TAPE POSITION FOR <CUT <AFTER INPUT.
.PARA
^THE <COF COMMAND ^CHANGES THE ^OUTPUT ^FILE FROM TERMINAL TO THE
SPECIFIED DEVICE  UNTIL CHANGED BY ANOTHER <COF COMMAND. ^THESE
DEVICES ARE VALID OBJECTS  FOR  THE  <COF  COMMAND: ^P^RINTER,
^T^E^RMINAL, ^T^E^LETYPE, AND A FILENAME IN THE DIRECTORY OF THE OPERATOR 
RUNNING THE <TITO PROGRAM.
^USE A FORM OF '<COF <FILENA.ME' IF IT IS NECESSARY TO OBTAIN AN ONLINE COPY OF
A TAPE DIRECTORY OR IF THE LINE PRINTER IS UNAVAILABLE AT THAT TIME.
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.SKIP 20
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
