ENTRY INTO THE PROGRAM
-----------------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
            '.'R TITO(CR)
                    'DEVICE:' FTAN(CR)     (N IS DRIVE NO.)

                    'TRACKS: 9'
                    'DENSITY (1600,6250):' 6250(CR)
                    "*"
                  (TITO IS NOW READY TO BEGIN ACCEPTING COMMANDS)
.SKIP 1
                        (OR, FOR 7 TRACK TAPES)
            '.'R TITO(CR)
                    'DEVICE:' FTA0(CR) 
                    'TRACKS: 7'                    (PRINTED BY TITO)
                    'DENSITY (800,556):' 800(CR)
                    "*"
                  (TITO IS NOW READY TO BEGIN ACCEPTING COMMANDS)
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 7
.INDEX <TITO <DIRECTORY <COMMAND
THE DIRECTORY COMMAND
----------------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
            "*"DIRECTORY ALL(CR)        (HOW MUCH TAPE TO SEARCH)
                    'INPUT TAPE POS. RANGE:' (CR)       (WHOLE TAPE)
                    'LAST KNOWN POS WAS 12'
.SKIP 1
        (OR YOU CAN GET A PARTIAL DIRECTORY WITH THIS INPUT:)
                    'INPUT TAPE POS. RANGE:' 1,3-5,11,15-E(CR)
.SKIP 1
        (UNLESS A <COF COMMAND IS USED THE DIR OUTPUTS ON TTY)
.SKIP 1
                    'THIS IS TAPE NO. 1 RECORDED 12:13 17-JUL-75
                    SYSTEM C35-P022/P DRIVE 145 800 BPI 7 TRACK
.SKIP 1
                    POSITION    FILE NAME      USER NAME
                        1  1   TITO  .CMD     YOUNGERC
                        3  1   USR   .CMD     YOUNGERC
                        4  1   COM   .MAC     YOUNGERC
                        5  1   CHR   .MAC     YOUNGERC
                       11  1   UUO   .MAC     YOUNGERC
                       15  1   BUG   .MAC     YOUNGERC
                       16  1   LOOKUP.MAC     YOUNGERC
                    TOTAL    7 FILES  FOR     YOUNGERC
.SKIP 1
                    TOTAL 7 FILES FOR SAVE SET.
.SKIP 1
                    LOGICAL EOT--NO SAVE SETS FOLLOW.'
.SKIP 5
