.LM 7
.INDEX <TITO <TRANSLATE <COMMAND
THE TRANSLATE COMMAND
----------------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
        (TRANSLATION CAN BE DONE WITHIN THE RESTORE COMMAND OR VIA THE
         TRANSLATE COMMAND)
.SKIP 1
               "*"RESTORE (GBLOOD)__(ABLE)TAP.MAC(CR)
.SKIP 1
               "*"RESTORE (GBLOOD)__(ABLE),(BURGESST)__(BAKER)(CR)
.SKIP 1
               "*"RESTORE (GBLOOD),(GBLOOD)__(ABLE)(CR)
.SKIP 1
          (IN THE CASE BELOW TRANSLATE IS DONE SEPARATELY)
.SKIP 1
               "*"TRANSLATE (ABLE)__(BAKER)(CR)
.SKIP 1
               "*"RESTORE #1,5,7-13(CR)
.SKIP 1
               (FILES IN GIVEN POSITIONS FROM USER BAKER
               WILL BE RESTORED TO USER ABLE ON DISK.
               FILES IN GIVEN POSITIONS WITH NAMES OTHER
               THAN BAKER WILL BE SKIPPED).
.SKIP 1
          (GIVEN A TRANSLATION TABLE, THE SAME RESTORE CAN BE DONE
           THIS WAY ALSO:)
.SKIP 1
               "*"RESTORE ALL(CR)
               'INPUT TAPE POS. RANGE:' 1,5,7-13(CR)
.SKIP 1
          THE TRANSLATE COMMAND CAN BE USED WITH AN INDIRECT FILE WITH
          A SEPARATE DISC/TAPE USERNAME PAIR ON EACH LINE:
.SKIP 1
               "*"TRANSLATE @TRA.CMD(CR)
.SKIP 1
               WHERE FILE TRA.CMD CONTAINS THE FOLLOWING:
.SKIP 1
               (ABLE)__(BAKER)(CR)
               (GBLOOD)__(ABLE)(CR)
               (BURGESST)__(BAKER)(CR)
.SKIP 10
.LM 7
