.LM 7
CONTINUING ON MULTIPLE TAPES
-----------------------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
          WHENEVER A STORE JOB ENCOUNTERS THE PHYSICAL END OF TAPE 
          A MESSAGE LIKE THE ONE BELOW WILL OUTPUT FROM TITO:
.SKIP 1
          'FILE (YOUNGERC)TAP.MAC WILL BE CONTINUED ON THE NEXT TAPE
          STARTING WITH BLOCK 192.  PARTIAL CKSUM: 14264,,223705
.SKIP 1
          "MOUNT NEXT TAPE"
          'CONTINUE ON DEVICE:' UNL(CR)          (UNLOAD THE FIRST TAPE)
          'CONTINUE ON DEVICE:' FTA2(CR)        (THEN INDICATE NEXT TAPE)
          'TRACKS: 9                       (THIS IS PRINTED BY TITO
                                            <NO OPER INPUT NEEDED)
          TAPE NUMBER 2 FOR 15:20 15-JUL-75
          STARTING WITH BLOCK 192 OF FILE (YOUNGERC)TAP.MAC'
.SKIP 1
          SHOULD THE SYSTEM CRASH OR THE STORE BE INTERRUPTED, YOU CAN
          RESTART THE JOB ON A NEW TAPE WITH A FORM OF THE NEXT 
          COMMAND STRING:
.SKIP 1
           "*"STO ALL STA W (MARCINJ)(CR)       (START WITH A USER E.G.
                                                 DURING AN ALL FILES STORE)
.SKIP 1
          TITO WILL ALLOW YOU TO CONTINUE MANUALLY FROM A SPECIFIC FILE:
.SKIP 1
          "*"STO ALL STA W (MARCINJ)ERA.SAV(CR)                     
.SKIP 1
          YOU CAN EVEN CONTINUE MANUALLY WITH A PARTIAL CHECKSUM ALTHOUGH
          THIS IS RISKY WITH REGARDS TO FILE INTEGRITY:
.SKIP 1
          "*"STO ALL STA W (MARCINJ)ERA.SAV_<200>_<405231,,37602>(CR) 
.SKIP 1
