.LM 7
RESTARTING ALLFILES AND DAILY BACKUPS
-------------------------------------
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
\\
^WHEN RUNNING <ALLFILES OR <DAILY BACKUP, AND FOR SOME REASON THE
JOB IS ABORTED, (I. E. ^SYSTEM ^CRASH, <NETWORK, ^POWER ^FAILURE, ETC)
THERE ARE TWO WAYS OF RESTARTING THE JOB.
.SKIP 1
^THE FIRST IS TO USE THE <CUT <AFTER <COMMAND.  ^THIS COMMAND IS USED
WHEN THE LAST FILE STORED IS SOMEWHERE BETWEEN THE MIDDLE OR NEAR THE
END OF THE TAPE.
.SKIP 1
^THE SECOND COMMAND IS <STORE <ALL <STARTING <WITH <_<BLOCK> AND
<_<PARTIAL <CKSUM>.  ^THIS COMMAND WOULD BE USED WHEN THE LAST
FILE STORED ON TAPE IS CLOSE TO THE BEGINNING OF THE TAPE.  ^TO
BE ABLE TO USE THIS COMMAND, THE <STORE WOULD HAVE TO BE ON THE <SECOND
<REEL OR BEYOND.
^^
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.INDEX <TITO <CUT <AFTER <EXAMPLE
.CENTER;EXAMPLE OF CUT AFTER COMMAND
.CENTER;----------------------------
.SKIP 1
"."R TITO (CR)
.SKIP 1
"TITO (CURRENT VERSION)(TIME/DATE)"
"SYSTEM (SYSTEM _#_#-MONITOR VERSION)"
"DEVICE:" FTA_# (CR)
"TRACKS:  _#"
"DENSITY (6250,1600):" 6250 (CR)
"TAPE NOT WRITE PROTECTED"
.SKIP 1
"*"NEW TAPE (CR)
"ARE YOU SURE?" Y (CR)
"*"STORE ALL CHANGE (CR)
.SKIP 1
"TAPE NUMBER 1 FOR (TIME/DATE)"
.SKIP 1
"(USERNAME) _# OF FILES."
.SKIP 1
(OTHER USERS BEING STORED TO TAPE)
.SKIP 1
(DANIELSR)  3 FILES.
.SKIP 1
"PLEASE LOG IN:"
.SKIP 1
(WHEN SYSTEM COMES BACK UP AND REGULAR PROCEDURES ARE FINISHED, CALL
 TITO).
.SKIP 1
AFTER "TAPE NOT WRITE PROTECTED" PRINTS OUT, ENTER REWIND AT THE
PROMPT.
