"*"REWIND (CR)
"*"COF (ENTER A FILENAME)(CR)
"NEW FILE?" Y (CR)
"*"DIR ALL (CR)
"INPUT TAPE POS RANGE" (CR)
.NOTE
IF TAPE SEEMS TO BE JUST JUMPING BACK AND FORTH, OR TAPE RUNS OFF
THE END OF REEL, HIT A _^C TWO TIMES.  AT THE PROMPT, TYPE IN <CLOSE.
.END NOTE
"FILE (DBADAVE)FILENAME HAD TOO LITTLE DATE ON TAPE"
"LOGICAL EOT--NO SAVE SETS FOLLOW"
"TOTAL _#_# FILES PROCESSED"
.SKIP 1
"*"REWIND (CR)
.NOTE
AT THIS POINT, PRINT THE DIRECTORY TO FIND OUT WHAT THE TAPE POSITION
WAS FOR THE LAST WHOLE FILE PROCESSED.  LAST WHOLE FILE WAS (DBADAVE)
FILENAME--POSITION 135)
.END NOTE
"*"CUT AFTER (DBADAVE)FILENAME (CR)
"INPUT TAPE POS RANGE" 135 (CR)
ARE YOUR SURE? Y
"CUT FINISHED--NOW POSITIONED AT LOGICAL EOT"
"*"STORE ALL CHANGED STARTING WITH (DBADAVE)FILENAME (CR)
"REEL NUMBER:" _#1 (CR)
.NOTE
YOU WILL START WITH THE FILE ON THE DIRECTORY THAT HAD AN ERROR WRITING
IT TO TAPE, OR YOU COULD RESTART IT WITH THE LAST KNOWN GOOD FILE STORED.
.END NOTE
"TAPE NUMBER _#1 FOR (TIME/DATE)"
.SKIP 1
THE BACKUP SHOULD NOW RUN IN ITS NORMAL MANNER.
