.FILL.JUST
.SKIP 1
^IF THE ABOVE MESSAGE IS RECEIVED WHEN STORING TO A TAPE, THEN DO
THE FOLLOWING:
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.LM 11
A.  <QUIT OUT OF <TITO.
.SKIP 1
B.  <REWIND THE TAPE AND WRITE A <DIRECTORY TO <DISK (<FTA_#.DIR).
    (_# = TAPE DRIVE NUMBER)
.SKIP 1
C.  UNLOAD THE TAPE AND QUIT OUT OF TITO.
.SKIP 1
D.  NEXT, TYPE 'R (XEXEC)TAIL;FTA_#.DIR.
.SKIP 1
E.  AFTER 'LOGICAL EOT' AND TOTAL (NUMBER) OF FILES PROCESSED PRINTS
    OUT, MOUNT NEXT TAPE TO BE USED.
.SKIP 1
F.  GET BACK INTO TITO.  RESTART THE STORE WITH THE LAST COMPLETE
    FILE THAT WAS STORED TO TAPE.
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
.CENTER;^&EXAMPLE\&
.SKIP 1
(WE9905X) START POS 42701 - (WE9905X) END POS 43003,  67 FILES
.SKIP 1
(WE9913X) START POS 43441 - EXCEEDED PROG LIMIT FOR NO. OF...ETC
.SKIP 1
'*'Q
