.LM 7
.INDEX <TITO <OVERWRITTEN <TAPES
.CENTER;^&RECREATION OF AN OVERWRITTEN TITO TAPE\&
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
^IF A TITO TAPE HAS BEEN MISTAKENLY INITIALEZED AS A NEW TAPE,
THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES SHOULD BE FOLLOWED TO SALVAGE AS MANY
FILES AS POSSIBLE.
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.SKIP 1
"R TITO"            ;APPEND TO THE END OF THE TAPE,
                    ;THEN "QUIT".
.SKIP 1
"R (UTIL)MAGCON"    ;THE INPUT SPECS ARE
"FILE:" FTA1:
"MODE" ASCII
"VARIABLE LENGTH RECORDS:" N
"CRLS'S IN ASCII FILE?" Y
"RECORD SIZE:" 80
"BLOCKING FACTOR:" 1
"STOP ON ERRORS?" Y
"DENSITY:" 6250
"ADVANCE FILES:" 2  ;IMPORTANT:  THIS ADVANCES
                    ;PAST EOF MARKER
"ADVANCE RECORDS:" 0
"REWIND:" OMIT
"LABEL:" NONE
"UNLOAD TAPE?" N
"MULTIPLE OUTPUT FILES FOR THIS INPUT FILE ?" N
.SKIP 1
"ALL INPUT SPECS CORRECT ?" Y
.SKIP 1
"OUTPUT SPECS ARE:"
"FILE:" TTY:
"STOP ON ERRORS?" Y
.SKIP 1
"ALL OUTPUT SPECS CORRECT ?" Y
.SKIP 1
"SUBSTITUTIONS ?" <NO
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
AFTER THE OUTPUT HAS TYPED OUT ON THE TERMINAL, TYPE <"CONTROL <C" (_^<C).
.PARA
TITO WRITES EOF MARKERS AT THE END OF EACH SAVE SET.  TO FIND
WHICH SAVE SET THE TAPES IS NOW POSITIONED, TYPE "R TITO", ENTER DEVICE
AND DENSITY, TYPE "RES (OPER)".  WHEN "INPUT TAPE POS RANGE:" TYPES OUT,
HIT ONLY ONE <"CONTROL <C" (_^<C).  THEN TYPE "WHERE".
.PARA
LOOK ON THE ORIGINAL TAPE DIRECTORY TO SEE WHICH SAVE SET THE TAPE
IS POSITIONED.  YOU WILL BE ABLE TO SALVAGE ALL FILES FROM THIS POINT.
IF MAY BE POSSIBLE TO SAVE SOME FILES FROM THE PREVIOUS SAVE SET ALSO.
IF THE PREVIOUS SAVE SET IS A DUPLICATE OF THE ONE THE TAPE IS POSITIONED,
DON'T BOTHER WITH THIS STEP.  IF YOU ARE AT POSITION 23, TRY RESTORING FROM
POSITION 22 BY TYPING:
.SKIP 3
.NOFILL.NOJUST
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
"*"RES (HOLD)^_(USERNAME)       ;USERNAME SHOULD BE FROM
                              ;TAPE DIRECTORY
"INPUT TAPE POS RANGE:" 22
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
IF THIS IS SUCCESSFUL, TRY POSITION 21, THEN 20, ETC.  WHEN YOU
RECEIVE THE MESSAGE "LOGICAL EOT -- NO SAVE SETS FOLLOW", YOU
HAVE COME TO THE EOF MARKER THAT WAS WRITTEN WHEN THE TAPE WAS
STARTED AS NEW.
.PARA
STORE THE FILES IN HOLD TO A NEW SCRATCH TAPE.  AFTER
THE FILES HAVE BEEN STORED TWICE, THEN DELETE THE HOLD FILES.
.PARA
POSITION THE TAPE TO THE FIRST GOOD SAVE SET BY FOLLOWING THE
"R TITO" AND "R (UTIL)MAGCON" PROCEDURES ABOVE.
.PARA
RESTORE ONE SAVE SET AT A TIME TO HOLD.  THEN APPEND THE
HOLD FILES TO A SCRATCH TAPE.  DELETE THE HOLD FILES.
.PARA
REPEAT THE ABOVE STEP UNTIL ALL SAVE SETS HAVE BEEN WRITTEN ONTO
THE SCRATCH TAPE.
.PARA
MAKE A DIRECTORY OF THE NEW TAPE.
.PARA
WRITE AN EXTERNAL LABEL ON THE TAPE SAYING, "THIS TAPE HAS BEEN
RECREATED, MUST USE TRANSLATE TO RESTORE".
.PARA
GIVE THE ORIGINAL TAPE TO YOUR SHIFT SUPERVISOR.
.PARA
NOTIFY THE CUSTOMER OF THE DAMAGE AND FILES NOT RECOVERED.
.SKIP 20
.NOFILL.NOJUST
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.INDEX <TITO <DEVICE <COMMAND
THE DEVICE COMMAND
-------------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
                  (SUPPOSING INITIAL DEVICE IS FTA0 - 7TRK, 800 BPI)
.SKIP 1
                    "*"DEV FTA1(CR)
                    'TRACKS: 9'                     (PRINTED BY TITO)
                    'DENSITY(1600,6250):' 6250(CR)
                   "*"          (NOW OUR TITO COMMANDS ARE DIRECTED TO
                                 FTA1 9 TRK 6250)
.SKIP 1
                    "*"DEV FTA0(CR)     (TO GO BACK TO FTA0)
                    "*"
.SKIP 1
.LM 7
.INDEX <TITO <MODE <COMMAND
THE MODE COMMAND
----------------
.LM 0
.SKIP 1
          "*"MODE(CR)           (TYPES THE CURRENT MODE - IN THIS CASE
          'STORE: USERS         THE DEFAULT MODE)
          RESTORE: USERS
          OLD FILES: CONFIRM
          OLD SYS FILES: CONFIRM'
