<TITO OUTPUT MESSAGES ARE NORMALLY DIRECTED TO THE TERMINAL RUNNING
THE PROGRAM; HOWEVER THE '<COF' (CHANGE OUTPUT FILE) CAN CAUSE THEM TO BE
DUPLICATED ELSEWHERE. ^THE ERROR MESSAGES LISTED BELOW WILL BE DIRECTED TO
THE CONTROLLING TERMINAL REGARDLESS OF ANY <COF SWITCH. ^BE SURE TO CHECK
FOR  ANY MESSAGES OF THE FORMAT  '<FILE <(FILENAME) <NOT <GIVEN <LICENSE
<XXXXXXXXX'. ^IN SOME CASES THIS CAN RESULT IN IMPORTANT SYSTEM JOBS
NOT BEING ABLE TO RUN. ^BE SURE TO CHECK ALL OUTPUT IF A DISK REBUILD OR  
REFRESH IS BEING DONE. ^HERE ARE THE <TITO ERROR MESSAGES:
