.FILL.JUST
^THE FOLLOWING IS A LIST OF MOST COMMON ERRORS THAT ^OPERATORS
WILL SEE WHILE RUNNING <TITO.  ^OPERATORS SHOULD PAY CLOSE ATTENTION TO
THEM AND CORRECTIVE ACTION SHOULD BE TAKEN, IF KNOWN, WHERE APPLICABLE.
^IN THIS REGARD, DON'T TRY TO CORRECT A PROBLEM IF YOU ARE NOT SURE
OF WHAT TO DO.  ^ALL <UNKNOWN <CORRECTIVE <ACTION SHOULD BE BROUGHT
TO THE ATTENTION OF YOUR ^SHIFT ^SUPERVISOR.  ^IF THE ^SHIFT ^SUPERVISOR
CANNOT SOLVE THE PROBLEM, THEN IT IS TO BE ESCULATED.
.SKIP 1
^HARDCOPY IS NEEDED AT ALL TIMES IF IT HAS TO BE RESEARCHED.
.SKIP 1
^SOME OF THE MOST COMMON MESSAGES THAT ^OPERATORS WILL SEE ARE:
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
^^
        A.  FILE NOT DUMPED (USERNAME)FILENAME, MARKED TO NOT
            DUMP.
.SKIP 1
            NO ACTION REQUIRED.
.SKIP 1
        B.  UNABLE TO MARK FILE (USERNAME)FILENAME AS DUMPED.
.SKIP 1
            FILE MAY BE OPENED.  SHOULD BE PICKED UP ON NEXT
            BACKUP.  NO ACTION REQUIRED.
.SKIP 1
        C.  NEW FILE (USERNAME)FILENAME NOT MARKED AS DUMPED.
.SKIP 1
            <USER IS EDITING FILE.  WILL BE PICKUP UP ON NEXT
            BACKUP.  NO ACTION REQUIRED.
.SKIP 1
        D.  UNABLE TO DO LOOKUP ON FILE (USERNAME)FILENAME.
            CONTINUING WITH NEXT FILE.
.SKIP 1
            IF THIS KEEPS PRINTING OUT ON A SINGLE, OR MULTIPLE
            USERNAME, THERE COULD BE A HARDWARE PROBLEM.  GET OUT
            OF TITO AND START CHECKING THE HARDWARE.  LOOK FOR
            CHECKED OUT BE NOVADYNE (FSC).  AFTER THE PROBLEM IS SOLVED,
            PUT THE TAPE INVOLVED BACK ON THE TAPE DRIVE AND
            MAKE A DIRECTORY OF TAPE.  USING THE DIRECTORY,
            WRITE AN EOT MARK AFTER THE LAST GOOD POSITION.
            PUT THIS TAPE ASIDE, AND MOUNT THE NEXT TAPE AND
            START WITH THE NEXT USERNAME.
.SKIP 1
        E.  FILE NOT DUMPED (USERNAME)FILENAME, MARKED BAD ON TAPE.
.SKIP 1
            THIS MEANS THE FILE MAY HAVE A HARDWARE DATA
            READ/WRITE ERROR, OR HAS BEEN FOUND BAD BY DAMAGE
            ASSESSMENT PROGRAM.  NO ACTION IS REQUIRED, BUT
            HARDCOPY SHOULD BE SAVED AND SENT TO THE SHIFT
            SUPERVISOR.
.SKIP 1
        F.  AN EXCESSIVE AMOUNT OF HUNG DEVICE ERRORS SHOULD
            BE BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF NOVADYNE (FSC).  THIS COULD
            BE A HARDWARE PROBLEM.  ^OPERATORS ARE TO WRITE AN 
            I/R (INCIDENT REPORT) ON THIS.
.SKIP 1
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
