^&TAKING SYSTEM DOWN\&
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
After performing all of the above, the system can be taken down using
these procedures:
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.LM 11
1.  Run TAKEIT with BOOTS-LOADED option.
.SKIP 1
2.  After the system is down at BOOTS:, press
    carriage return to load the current running SYSTEM.SAV.
.LM 7
.FILL.JUST
.NOTE
If system is suppose to be up on NEWMON, enter NEWMON at the BOOTS:
prompt and then press carriage return.
.END NOTE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.LM 11
3.  After the monitor has loaded, the system is at ONCE> dialogue
    mode.  (Be careful while in this mode).
.SKIP 1
4.  At the ONCE> prompt, enter CONSOLE and a carriage return.
.SKIP 1
5.  At the next ONCE> prompt, enter READONLY (CR).
.SKIP 1
6.  Do a CTRL-Z L and type in OPER and a carriage return.
    (CTRL-Z, L, and OPER will not output to CTY/TTY).
.SKIP 6
.LM 7
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
.LM 11
7.  After the carriage return is entered, 'please log in:' will
    output along with the statement:
.SKIP 1
    'date not set, type date as mm-dd-yyyy'
.SKIP 1
    Enter date as:  04-27-1987 (CR)
.SKIP 1
8.  The next statement that outputs is:
.SKIP 1
    'type time as hh:mm'
.SKIP 1
    Enter time as: 08:00 (CR)
.SKIP 1
9.  SET STATUS and then change schedule to 600000.
.SKIP 6
.LM 7
10. At the TYMCOM-10 prompt (!), enter:
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
'!'R ASP (CR)                  ;This command to be
                               ;used on all Hosts
.NOTE
For commands to be entered next, see SAMPLE on next page.
.END NOTE
.INDEX <ASP <BRINGING <SYSTEM <UP
.LM 11
