     this, enter the following commands:
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
'.' SP (CR)
'>.' P BOTLOD (CR)
'>.' GO (CR)
'>.'
.LM 7
.FILL.JUST
.NOTE
If system is suppose to be up on NEWMON, enter NEWMON at the BOOTS:
prompt and then press carriage return.  Enter GO at the ONCE> prompt.
.END NOTE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
