IV.C  Additional Commands
.INDEX <MAGCON <ADDITIONAL <COMMANDS
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 18
.PARAGRAPH -8
BYE     MAGCON returns to monitor level, resets all I/O, and
logs the user off the system.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
DIALOG  Returns user to dialog mode.  MAGCON will ask the user
questions about the input and output file specifications
according to the explanation in Section II.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
ERASE   This command causes the current retained command
to be deleted and returns MAGCON to the immediate mode of
operation; MAGCON will go back to executing
commands as they are typed.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
EXIT    MAGCON returns to monitor level and resets all I/O.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
PRINT   Types out the current retained command.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
RETAIN  Used to save a subsequent command.  In this mode, the
next command entered is not executed immediately.  Instead,
MAGCON saves the command line and allows the user to edit
it.  To edit the command string, the user need only retype the
part of the command he/she wishes to change.  Items that
follow the back arrow or equal sign will be edited to the
input side of the command, while items that precede the back
arrow or equal sign will be edited to the output side of the
command.
.SKIP 1
.PAR -8
REWIND  Rewinds the specified magnetic tape.  MAGCON
will prompt for the device to be rewound (the device name must be
terminated with a colon ":".  In this way, a tape may be rewound
without transferring any data.
.SKIP 1
RUN     Performs the current retained command.
.SKIP 1
QUIT    Same function as EXIT.
.LEFT MARGIN 10
.PAR 0
.SKIP 1
The following commands may be input to MAGCON during a file
transfer.  Unless noted, they will not affect the transfer.
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 18
.PAR -8
FILES   Prints the input and output file specifications for
the user.
.skip 4
.LM 7
.NOFILL.NOJUST
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
.LM 18
.PAR -8
.FILL.JUST
PAUSE   Exits to the monitor level.  MAGCON may
be continued with the CONTINUE command.

STOP    Closes files and returns to MAGCON command level -- stops
the data transfer.

WHAT    Prints the input and output file specifications and
statistics associated with the transfer to the user.
.SKIP 40
.LM 7
.NOFILL.NOJUST
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
