<MAGCON <BUGS
.SKIP 1
^WHEN YOU ARE CONVERTING FROM DISK TO TAPE YOU CAN USE *.* TO
REFER TO ALL FILES IN A GIVEN DIRECTORY.
^HOWEVER, TO STORE ALL THE FILES A SECOND TIME (I.E., <REPEAT
<SPECS?), ONLY THE FIRST FILE IN THE DIRECTORY WILL BE STORED ON TAPE.
^TO GET AROUND THIS, ANSWER <YES TO THE QUESTION:
^^
"<CHANGE <INPUT <SPECS?" AND "<CHANGE <OUTPUT <SPECS?"
\\
^WHAT YOU "CHANGE" IS MERELY TO TYPE IN *.* AGAIN.
.SKIP 1
<MAGCON WON'T WRITE A LOGICAL END OF TAPE MARK; THIS IS NOT REALLY
A PROBLEM, BUT IT MEANS THAT IT IS IMPOSSIBLE TO <APPEND TO A
<MAGCON TAPE.
.SKIP 1
^THE <LABELS OPTION DOES NOT WORK.
^IF YOU USE IT, YOU'LL GET GARBAGE ON THE TAPE INSTEAD OF LABELS.
