.PARAGRAPH
^ANY OF THE MANY OPTIONS AVAILABLE IN <PIP MAY BE SELECTED BY USE OF A SWITCH.
^SWITCHES THAT DO NOT REFERENCE MAGTAPE ARE PRECEDED IN THE COMMAND STRING
WITH A SLASH (/); MAGTAPE SWITCHES ARE ENCLOSED IN PARENTHESIS AND MUST BE
TYPED IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING THE DEVICE TO WHICH THEY REFER.
^IF MORE THAN ON SWITCH IS USED ON EITHER THE DESTINATION OF SOURCE
HALVES OF THE COMMAND STRING THEY ARE ENCLOSED IN PARENTHESIS.
^BELOW IS A LIST OF <PIP SWITCHES THAT ARE MOST OFTEN USED.
(^THE FULL LIST CAN BE FOUND IN THE DOCUMENT MENTIONED ABOVE.)
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.SKIP 1
.TS 8,25
	<MAGTAPE
	<SWITCH	<EFFECT
	------	------
.SKIP 1
	(^M6)	^SET TAPE DENSITY AT 6250 <BPI (9<TRK DEFAULT)
	(^M1)	^SET TAPE DENSITY AT 1600 <BPI
	(^M8)	^SET TAPE DENSITY AT 800 <BPI (7<TRK DEFAULT)
	(^M5)	^SET TAPE DENSITY AT 556 <BPI
	(<ME)	^SET PARITY EVEN (ODD PARITY IS THE DEFAULT)
	(<MA)	^ADVANCE THE TAPE 1 FILE
	(^M_#N^A)	^ADVANCE THE TAPE N (SOME NUMBER) FILES
	(<MB)	^BACKSPACE THE TAPE 1 FILE
	(^M_#N^B)	^BACKSPACE THE TAPE N FILES
	(<MW)	^REWIND THE TAPE
	(<MT)	^SKIP TO THE LOGICAL <END-^O^F-^T^A^P^E
	(<MF)	^MARK AN <END-^O^F-^F^I^L^E
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
	<NON-^M^A^G^T^A^P^E
	<SWITCH	<EFFECT
	-----------	------
.SKIP 1
	/^B	^INITIALIZE DEVICES IN <BINARY <MODE; TRANSFER
		DATA ONE WORD AT A TIME, NO INTERPRETATION.
	/^C	^DELETE TRAILING SPACES; CONVERT MULTIPLE SPACES
		TO TABS.
	/^E	^REPLACE CHARS. 73 THRU 80 WITH SPACES (MAINLY
		USED WITH <CDR).
	/^G	^IGNORE (SKIP OVER) ALL ^I/^O ERRORS.
	/^H	^INITIALIZE DEVICES IN <IMAGE <BINARY <MODE.
	/^I	^INITIALIZE DEVICES IN <IMAGE <MODE.
	/^L	^LIST A DIRECTORY OF THE SOURCE DEVICE.
	/^N	^DELETE SEQUENCE NUMBERS FROM SOURCE FILE.
	/^O	^INSERT SEQUENCE NUMBERS AT THE BEGINNING OF
		EACH LINE.  ^START WITH 00000, INCREMENT BY 1.
.SKIP 5
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
	/^P	^INTERPRET FIRST CHAR. OF EACH  LINE AS A <
		<FORTRAN CARRIAGE CONTROL CHARACTER.
	/^S	^INSERT SEQUENCE NUMBERS AT THE BEGINNING OF
		EACH LINE.  ^START WITH 00010, INCREMENT BY 10.
	/^T	^DELETE TRAILING SPACES IN EACH LINE.
	/^X	^TRANSFER FILES AS INDIVIDUAL FILES.  (^DO NOT
		COMBINE SEVERAL SOURCE FILES INTO ONE DESTI-
		NATION FILE.)
.SKIP 1
((<COMMAND <DESCRIPTION))
