.NOFILL.NOJUST
^COPYING ^FILES FROM <DISK TO <DISK:
.SKIP 1
	*<DSK:[1,4]^T^O^T^A^L^S.^D^A^T __ <DSK:^PART1.DAT,^PART2.DAT(CR)
	^THIS TRANSFERS <PART1.^D^A^T AND <PART2.^D^A^T FROM THE DIRECTORY
	OF THE USER RUNNING THE PROGRAM INTO A SINGLE FILE <TOTALS.^D^A^T
	IN THE DIRECTORY OF THE USER WHOSE <PPN IS 1,4.
.SKIP 1
	*<DSK:/^X/^S[12,576]*.* __ <DSK:[1,6]*.*(CR)
	^COPIES ALL FILES IN [1,6] TO THE DIRECTORY WITH <PPN 12,576
	AND INSERTS SEQUENCE NUMBERS INCREMENTED BY 10 IN EACH FILE.
.SKIP 1
^READING ^CARDS TO <DISK:
.SKIP 1
	*<DSK:[132,5763]^CARDS.FT4/^E __ <CDR:(CR)
	^READS CARDS INTO A FILE NAMED <CARDS.^F^T4 FOR <PPN 132,5763
	USING THE SWITCH THAT REPLACES POSITIONS 73 THRU 80 ON THE
	CARDS WITH SPACES ON THE DISK FILE.
.SKIP 1
	*<FTA0:(^M8) __ <CDR:/^T(CR)
	^READS CARD DECK ONTO A FILE ON MAGTAPE MOUNTED ON 0 AND
	STRIPS OFF THE TRAILING BLANKS FROM EACH CARD READ.
.SKIP 1
.CENTER
(<NOTE:  <PIP WILL REPORT THE NUMBER OF CARDS READ.)
.SKIP 1
^READING AND ^WRITING ^MAGTAPES:
.SKIP 1
	*<DSK:[1,15]/^X/^B __ <FTA1:(^M8)^DATA.BIN,^DATA1,BIN,^DATA3.BIN(CR)
	^FROM <FTA1 AT 800 <BPI, THE FILES <DATA.^B^I^N, <DATA1.^B^I^N AND
	<DATA3.^B^I^N ARE RESTORED AS SEPARATE FILES TO THE DIRECTORY WITH
	<PPN 1,15; THE FILES ARE RESTORED IN <BINARY <MODE.
.SKIP 1
	*^F^T^A0:(^M8)/^X __ <DSK:[2,24]*.SYM(CR)
	^STORES ALL FILES IN 2,24 WITH THE <SYM EXTENSION AS SEPARATE
	FILES ON TAPE UNIT 0 AT 800 <BPI.
.SKIP 1
	*^F^T^A0:(<MW) __ (CR)
	^REWINDS <FTA0.
.SKIP 1
^READING AND ^WRITING ^PAPER ^TAPES:
.SKIP 1
	*<PTP:/^I __ [234,567]^F^I^L^E^X.^F^O^O(CR)
	^PUNCHES A PAPER TAPE IN <IMAGE <MODE OF THE FILE <FILEX.^F^O^O.
.SKIP 1
	*<DSK:[1,2]^FROM.TAP __ <PTR:(CR)
	^READS FROM <PAPER <TAPE <READER TO A FILE IN 1,2 NAMED <FROM.^T^A^P.
