.PARAGRAPH
^IF ANY ERROR OCCURS WHILE RUNNING <PIP, THE OPERATION WILL BE ABORTED
AND THE DIAGNOSTIC MESSAGE WILL BE PRECEDED BY A QUESTION MARK (?).
^ON THE OTHER HAND, IF THE /^G SWITCH HAS BEEN USED, THE PROGRAM
WILL IGNORE THE ERROR AND ATTEMPT TO CONTINUE EXECUTION.
^BE AWARE OF ERRORS THAT OCCUR IN THE OUTPUT DEVICE.
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.TS 8,30
	^THERE ARE 5 TYPES OF ERROR DIAGNOSTICS THAT CAN OCCUR IN <PIP:
.SKIP 1
	<ERROR
	<STRING	<MEANING
	------	-------
.SKIP 1
	^C	^A COMMAND STRING ERROR HAS OCCURRED.
	<FR	^A FILE REFERENCE ERROR HAS OCCURRED.
	^I/^O	^AN INPUT/OUTPUT ERROR HAS OCCURRED.
	<RIM	^A <READ-^I^N-^M^O^D^E SPECIFICATION ERROR.
	^S	^ALL OTHER TYPES OF ERRORS.
.FILL.JUST
.PARAGRAPH
^HERE ARE SOME OF THE ERROR STRINGS THAT CAN PROVIDE DIAGNOSTIC
HELP IN DETERMINING WHY A <PIP COMMAND FAILED:
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
?<DEVICE <DEV: <DOES <NOT <EXIST
	^I/^O - ^EITHER THE DEVICE NAME HAS BEEN MISSPELLED OR THE DEVICE
	DOES NOT EXIST.
.SKIP 1
?<DEVICE <DEV: <NOT <AVAILABLE
	^I/^O - ^THE DEVICE HAS NOT BEEN PROPERLY ASSIGNED OR IS ASSIGNED
	TO ANOTHER JOB.
.SKIP 1
?<ILLEGAL <DENSITY <SPECIFIED <ON <TAPE <DEVICE
	^I/^O - ^THE DENSITY SPECIFIED IS NOT AVAILABLE ON THAT DRIVE.
.SKIP 1
?<FILE <FILENAME.^E^X^T <ILLEGAL <FORMAT
	<RIM - ^ZERO LENGTH FILE, JOB DATA INFO NOT AVAILABLE, BLOCK OVER-
	LAPS PREVIOUS BLOCK OR <EOF FOUND WHEN DATA WAS EXPECTED.
.SKIP 1
?<FILENAME.^E^X^T <FILE <WAS <BEING <MODIFIED
	<FR - ^DISK FILE NAMED WAS BEING USED BY SOME OTHER JOB; TRY AGAIN
	LATER.
.SKIP 1
?<FILENAME.^E^X^T <FILE <WAS <NOT <FOUND
	<FR - ^THE FILE SPECIFIED WAS NOT FOUND DURING A LOOKUP.
.SKIP 1
?<FILENAME.^E^X^T <INCORRECT <PROJECT-^P^R^O^G^R^A^M^M^E^R <NUMBER
	<FR - ^THE <PPN GIVEN FOR A DISK FILE IS INCORRECT.
.SKIP 5
<BTNA ^TAPE ^PROCEDURES
^REVISION 2; 10/21/93
.PAGE
?<INPUT <DEVICE <DEV: <FILE <FILENAME.^E^X^T
	^I/^O - ^ANOTHER MESSAGE FOLLOWS (SEE BELOW).
.SKIP 1
?<LINE <TOO <LONG
	^A LINE GREATER THAN 140 CHARACTERS WAS FOUND IN THE SOURCE FILE.
.SKIP 1
?<NO <FILE <NAMED <FILENAME.^E^X^T
	<FR - ^NO SUCH FILE WAS FOUND WHEN <PIP SEARCHED THE DIRECTORY.
.SKIP 1
?<OUTPUT <DEVICE <DEV: <FILE <FILENAME.^E^X^T
	^I/^O - ^ANOTHER MESSAGE FOLLOWS (SEE BELOW).
.SKIP 1
?<PIP <COMMAND <ERROR
	^C - ^EITHER AN ILLEGAL <PIP COMMAND STRING, A NON-EXISTENT SWITCH,
	OR A FILENAME OTHER THAN *.* WAS REQUESTED FOR A DEVICE THAT
	DOES NOT HAVE A DIRECTORY (E.G. <PTR, <PTP, <CDR).
.SKIP 1
     ^THE FOLLOWING ARE <PIP SECONDARY ^I/^O DIAGNOSTIC MESSAGES.
^THEY MAY ACCOMPANY ONE OF THE ERROR MESSAGES LISTED ABOVE.
